&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/simple-icons/simple-icons&quot;&gt;Simple Icons&lt;/a&gt; is what I am talking about. Accidently, stumbed onto these while searching for alternative icons than what was including in this theme for Jekyll. They show both the icon in svg format which cleanly expands at any size and the color which the icon should be. However, what they don’t explain is how to apply the color to pure html, which is not a big deal. Just requires basic css style which I give hats off to: &lt;a href=&quot;http://tutorials.jenkov.com/svg/fill.html&quot;&gt;Jenkov.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;h2 id=&quot;the-how&quot;&gt;The How&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you checked out the above link you would get the idea. The only downfall I found is that you can’t just link the svg as an image to color it, you have to use the actually SVG code. Simple as downloading the icons you want above and just opening them with a text editor and copy the code. So not going to go to much into it and just show you the code for the most commonly used icons (Google+ moved to business only):&lt;/p&gt;

